## The Execution Protocol

### Weekly Cadence (2–3 hours/week minimum)

**Monday (30 min):** Check notifications on repos you've contributed to. Respond to PR reviews, comment on new issues.

**Wednesday (60 min):** Work on your next PR. Research, draft, and submit.

**Friday (30 min):** Engage with the community — comment on other people's PRs, answer questions in issues, participate in discussions.

### Contribution Quality Standards

Every PR you submit must:

- Follow the repo's CONTRIBUTING guide exactly (formatting, commit messages, PR template)
- Be small and focused — one change per PR, not a massive dump
- Include a clear description of WHY the change matters, not just what it is
- Reference relevant clinical evidence or professional experience where appropriate
- Be reviewed by you at least twice before submitting

### What NOT to Do

- Do not submit massive PRs that rewrite entire sections — they won't get reviewed
- Do not argue with maintainers about merge decisions — accept feedback gracefully, iterate
- Do not claim expertise you don't have — stick to your clinical and operational knowledge lane
- Do not disappear after 2 weeks — consistency matters more than volume
- Do not submit AI-generated content without thorough personal review and clinical validation

